article.headline: Sacred Heart 82, Robert Morris 69
article.story: hodlbl CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- Ryan Litke scored 23 points and two other Sacred Heart players were in double figures as the Pioneers beat Robert Morris 82-69 on Sunday. Brice Brooks added 17 points and 11 rebounds for Sacred Heart, while Chauncey Hardy chipped in 13 points. Sacred Heart jumped out to a 42-39 lead with a three-pointer by Chauncey Hardy with 15:28 remaining. The Pioneers held a lead for the rest of the game. A.J. Jackson had 22 points and 10 rebounds to lead the Colonials, while Tony Lee added 18 points for the team.
